11/9/21, 15:26 - Kinjal ‚òÆÔ∏è: Ok
11/9/21, 15:27 - Kinjal ‚òÆÔ∏è: #include <stdio.h>

int main()
{
    int l,u, _sum=0;
    printf("Enter lower range\n");
    scanf("%d", &l);
    printf("Enter upper range\n");
    scanf("%d", &u);
    for(int i=l; i<=u; i++)
        {
        for(int j=1; j<i; j++)
        {
            if(i%j==0){
                _sum+=j;
            }
        }
        if(_sum==i & _sum!=0){
            printf("%d ", i);
        }
        _sum = 0;
    }
}

11/14/21, 02:55 - +91 74396 46126: #include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main()
{
    int x,n,i,j;
    printf ("Enter the value of x: ");
    scanf("%d", &x);
    printf ("Enter the number of terms: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);
    float S = 0;
    for (i=1; i<=n; i++)
    {
        float t = 1;
        for (j=1; j<=(2*i)-1; j++)
            t= t*x*1.0/j;
        if (i%2==0)
            S= S-t;
        else
            S= S+t;
    }
    printf ("The sum of the series is: %f", S);
    return 0;
}

12/7/21, 22:45 - +91 89100 20967: #include<stdio.h>

int main(){
    int r,c,n, space;
    printf("Enter the number of rows: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);
    
    
    
    for(r=1; r<=2*n-1; r++)
    {
            if(r<=n){
               for(space=1; space<=r; space++){
                printf(" ");
            }
            for(c=1; c<=(2*n-1)+2*(1-r); c++)
            {
                printf("*");
            }
            printf("\n"); 
            }
        else{
            for(space=1; space<=n-(r-n); space++){
            printf(" ");
            }
            for(c=1; c<=2*(r-n)+1; c++)
            {
                printf("*");
            }
            printf("\n"); 
            }
        
    }
}

3/31/22, 11:55 - +91 81012 31016: Hello everyone üíÉ

The much awaited auditions for the *Ghungroo Dance Club* have arrived. The *Round 1* auditions have been finalised on 7th April, 11:45 am onwards at CB 607 and the selected participants shall go through a *second round* of auditions on 8th April, 1:00pm onwards at CB 510. As you all know, the dance club has two wings - *HITKREW* (Western team) and *HITDIVA* (Eastern team). So it's your chance to audition for either of them. 

You will be given 1 minute, STRICTLY, to perform and the panel will judge you on your Expressions(10), Energy(10) and Style(10). Thus, it is imperative of you to carefully choose the best 60 seconds from any choreography/track/music. The choreography can be anything of your choice, although we'll highly appreciate if you choreograph it yourself & retain your authenticity. *There is no hard and fast rule regarding costume - whatever you feel comfortable in.*

The tracks need to be submitted beforehand to Ashutosh on WhatsApp - +91 97757 37098 . *Kindly take a note of this, because sending your tracks beforehand to Ashutosh is of utmost importance.*

(If you have any lab/class in the second half kindly notify us in the given WhatsApp number below.)

Date : 7th April
Time : 11:45 am onwards
Venue : CB 607
Reporting Time : 11:30am
Time limit : 1 min (Choreo of your choice)
Dress Code : Anything of your Comfort.
Tracks to be sent to Ashutosh on WhatsApp - +91 97757 37098

https://forms.gle/jNcjFXQUd9qkLRxD6

See you all on 7th April !

If you are an aspiring front-end developer, and are about to take the next step in your journey by learning React, I humbly invite you to join me in this hands-on workshop to learn the fundamentals of React and understand how to implement and build practical web applications!

Things you will learn in this hands-on workshop -

1. Understand why React is so popular.
2. Get familiar with JSX syntax.
3. React folder and file structure.
4. Learn how to use components and props.
5. React hooks such as useState and useEffect.
6. Fetching data from an external API.
7. Integrsting Tailwind CSS into your React application!

What are the prerequisites??

It would be awesome if you are familiar with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. You don't have to be an expert in Js. As long as you have the fundamentals clear, this workshop will be quite easy for you to follow! If you just want to join in and witness the incredible power to React, then you are welcome as well!

Mode: Microsoft Teams

12/18/22, 20:24 - Kinjal ‚òÆÔ∏è: *Kashiyatra'23*

Kashiyatra, the annual socio-cultural festival of IIT(BHU) Varanasi is a three day fiesta, aimed towards mesmerizing everyone with enchanting literary, musical and artistic events. It is the largest cultural festival of northern India. IIT(BHU) rests within Asia's biggest residential university, BHU in the holy city of Varanasi. Varanasi, the eternal city, houses plethora of traditions and has an ecstatic blend of cultures of myriad races. IIT(BHU) Varanasi has been nationally acclaimed for imparting technical knowledge in diverse fields and it has recently concluded its centenary celebrations.

*Registration and Payments*


1. Open kashiyatra.org 
2. Click on Register Now!
3. Click on Sign Up.
4. Fill up the Form (Enter Referral code of CA if you have any in the field of referral code)
5. Know your KYID on Dashboard.
6. Pay to the Kashiyatra official Bank Account via  different means as mentioned in website 
7. Upon successful registration do Register for events you want to participate (if any)

*Referral code*: KYCA0356

*Payment Structure upon using referral code*

Rs ~2000~ *1850* (participation + pro nite passes+ certificate+ 3-day accomodation without food + t-shirt )

Rs ~2500~ *2200* (participation +pro nite passes+ certificate+ 3-day accomodation with food+ t-shirt)

#include<stdlib.h>

double max=0.0,min=0.0,avg=0.0;

    int i,j;

        printf("%d",arr[i]);
        
    }
    printf("\n");
}
void swap(int *a,int *b){
    int temp;
    temp=*a;
    *a=*b;
    *b=temp;
}
void allpermutation(int *arr, int start, int end){
    int i;
    FILE * fp;
    if(start==end){
        fp=fopen("input.txt","a+");
        if(fp!=NULL){
            for(i=0;i<=end;i++){
            fprintf(fp,"%d ",arr[i]);
            
            }
        fprintf(fp,"\n");
        }
        fclose(fp);
    }
    
    else{
        for(i=start;i<=end;i++){
            swap((arr+i),(arr+start));
            allpermutation(arr,start+1,end);
            swap((arr+i),(arr+start));
        }
    }
}
int partition(int *arr,int low, int high){
    int pivot=arr[high];
    int i=(low-1),temp,j;
    for(j=low;j<=high-1;j++){
        if(arr[j]<=pivot){
            count++;
            i++;
            temp=arr[i];
            arr[i]=arr[j];
            arr[j]=temp;
        }
    }
    temp=arr[i+1];
    arr[i+1]=arr[high];
    arr[high]=temp;
    return (i+1);
}
int partition_r(int *arr,int low,int high){
    srand(time(NULL));
    int random=low+rand()%(high-low);
    int temp=arr[random];
    arr[random]=arr[high];
    arr[high]=temp;
    return partition(arr,low,high);
}
int random_select(int *arr,int low, int high,int rank){
    if(low<high){
        int pi=partition_r(arr,low,high);
        if(pi==rank-1){
            return pi;
        }
        else if(pi<rank){
            random_select(arr,pi+1,high,rank);
        }
        else{
            random_select(arr,low,pi-1,rank);
        }
    }
}
int main(){
    FILE *fp,*fp1;
    printf("Enter size");
    scanf("%d",&size);
    int i,r,rank;
    int arr[size];
    for(i=0;i<size;i++){
        scanf("%d",&arr[i]);
        
    }
    printf("enter rank to search for: ");
    scanf("%d",&rank);
    allpermutation(arr,0,size-1);
    fp=fopen("input.txt","r");
    while(!feof(fp)){
        for(i=0;i<size;i++){
            fscanf(fp,"%d ",&arr[i]);
        }
        count=0;
        r=random_select(arr,0,size-1,rank);
        fp1=fopen("write.txt","a+");
        fprintf(fp1,"%d %d %d \n",r,arr[r],count);
        fclose(fp1);;
    }
    fclose(fp);
    return 0;
}

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>

struct node
{
    int u;
    struct node *next;
};

void adjacency_matrix(int ver_count, int flag_dir)
{
    int i, j, u, v, w;
    int **adj_mat = (int **)malloc(sizeof(int *) * ver_count);
    for(i = 0; i < ver_count; i++)
    {    
        adj_mat[i] = (int *)malloc(sizeof(int) * ver_count);
        for(j = 0; j < ver_count; j++)
            adj_mat[i][j] = 0;
    }
    FILE *fptr = fopen("edge_input.txt", "r");
    while(!feof(fptr))
    {
        fscanf(fptr, "%d %d %d\n", &u, &v, &w);
        adj_mat[u][v] = 1;
        if(flag_dir == 0)
            adj_mat[v][u] = 1;
    }
    fclose(fptr);
    for(i = 0; i < ver_count; i++)
    {
        for(j = 0; j < ver_count; j++)
            printf("%d\t", adj_mat[i][j]);
        printf("\n");
    }
}

void insertBeg(struct node **head, int ver, int wt)
{
    struct node *ptr = (struct node *)malloc(sizeof(struct node));
    ptr->u = ver;
    ptr->next = *head;
    *head = ptr;
}

void adjacency_list(int ver_count, int flag_dir)
{
    int i, u, v, w;
    struct node **list = (struct node **)malloc(sizeof(struct node *) * ver_count), *ptr;
    for(i = 0; i < ver_count; i++)
    {    
        list[i] = (struct node *)malloc(sizeof(struct node));
        list[i] = NULL;
    }
    FILE *fptr = fopen("edge_input.txt", "r");
    while(!feof(fptr))
    {
        fscanf(fptr, "%d %d %d\n", &u, &v, &w);
        insertBeg(&list[u], v, w);
        if(flag_dir == 0)
            insertBeg(&list[v], u, w);
    }
    fclose(fptr);
    for(i = 0; i < ver_count; i++)
    {
        printf("\nThe neighbours of vertex %d is : ", i);
        ptr = list[i];
        while(ptr != NULL)
        {
            printf("%d ", ptr->u);
            ptr = ptr->next;
        }
    }
}

int main()
{
    int u, v, w, l = 0, temp_l, dir;
    FILE *fptr = fopen("edge_input.txt", "r");
    while(!feof(fptr))
    {
        fscanf(fptr, "%d %d %d\n", &u, &v, &w);
        temp_l = (int)fmax(u, v);
        l = (int)fmax(temp_l, l);
    }
    fclose(fptr);
    printf("\nSize of graph is %d\n", l+1);
    printf("\nIs the graph directed? Enter 0 for undirected and 1 for directed : ");
    scanf("%d", &dir);
    printf("\nThe adjacency matrix for the graph is given by :\n");
    adjacency_matrix(l+1, dir);
    printf("\nThe adjacency list for the graph is given by :");
    adjacency_list(l+1, dir);
}
2/16/23, 11:52 - +91 98745 39743: Merge sort:

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <ctype.h>
#include <string.h>

int count = 0;

void swap(int *a, int *b)
{
    int temp = *a;
    *a = *b;
    *b = temp;
}

void merge(int *arr, int l, int mid, int r)
{
    int i, j, k, n1, n2, *la, *ra;
    n1 = mid - l + 1;
    n2 = r - mid;
    la = (int *)malloc(sizeof(int) * n1);
    ra = (int *)malloc(sizeof(int) * n2);
    for(i = 0; i < n1; i++)
        *(la+i) = *(arr+(l+i));
    for(j = 0; j < n2; j++)
        *(ra+j) = *(arr+(mid+1+j));
    i = 0;
    j = 0;
    k = l;
    while(i < n1 && j < n2)
    {
        if(*(la+i) <= *(ra+j))
        {
            *(arr+k) = *(la+i);
            i++;
        }
        else
        {
            *(arr+k) = *(ra+j);
            j++;
        }
        k++;
        count++;
    }
    while(i < n1)
    {
        *(arr+k) = *(la+i);
        i++;
        k++;
    }
    while(j < n2)
    {
        *(arr+k) = *(ra+j);
        j++;
        k++;
    }
}

void mergesort(int *arr, int l, int r)
{
    if(l < r)
    {
        int mid = l + (r-l)/2;
        mergesort(arr, l, mid);
        mergesort(arr, mid+1, r);
        merge(arr, l, mid, r);
    }
}

void permutation(int *arr, int l, int r)
{
    
    FILE *fptr = fopen("mergesort_permutation.txt", "a");
    if(l == r)
    {
        for (int i = 0; i <= r; i++)
            fprintf(fptr, "%d\t", arr[i]);
        fprintf(fptr, "\n");
    }
    else
    {
        for(int i = l; i <= r; i++)
        {
            swap(&arr[i],  &arr[l]);
            permutation(arr, l+1, r);
            swap(&arr[i],  &arr[l]);
        }
    }
    fclose(fptr);
}

void mergesort_run(int n)
{
    FILE *fptr = fopen("mergesort_permutation.txt", "r"), *fout = fopen("mergesort_sort_out.txt", "w");
    char *c = (char *)malloc(sizeof(char) * (2*n + 2)), *token;
    int *a = (int *)malloc(sizeof(int) * n), i = 0;
    while(fgets(c, (2*n+2), fptr))
    {
        token = strtok(c, "\t\n");
        while(token != NULL)
        {
            *(a+i) = atoi(token);
            token = strtok(NULL, "\t\n");
            i++;
        }
        mergesort(a, 0, n-1);
        for(i = 0; i < n; i++)
            fprintf(fout, "%d\t", a[i]);
        fprintf(fout, "%d\n", count);
        i = 0;
        count = 0;
    }
    fclose(fout);
    fclose(fptr);
}

int main()
{
    FILE *fptr = fopen("mergesort_permutation.txt", "w");
    fclose(fptr);
    int n, *arr;
    printf("Enter size of array : ");
    scanf("%d", &n);
    arr = (int *)malloc(sizeof(int) * n);
    printf("Enter elements into the array :\n");
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        scanf("%d", &(*(arr+i)));
    permutation(arr, 0, n-1);
    mergesort_run(n);
    return 0;
}
2/16/23, 11:54 - +91 98745 39743: Heap Sort:

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <ctype.h>

int count = 0;

void swap(int *a, int *b)
{
    int temp = *a;
    *a = *b;
    *b = temp;
}

void maxheapify(int *arr, int root_index, int size)
{
    int left_index = 2 * root_index + 1;
    int right_index = 2 * root_index + 2;
    int largest_index = root_index;
    if(left_index < size && arr[left_index] > arr[largest_index])
    {    
        largest_index = left_index;
        count++;
    }
    if(right_index < size && arr[right_index] > arr[largest_index])
    {    
        largest_index = right_index;
        count++;
    }
    if(largest_index != root_index)
    {
        swap(&arr[largest_index], &arr[root_index]);
        maxheapify(arr, largest_index, size);
    }
}

void buildheap(int *arr, int size)
{
    int parent_index = (int)(size - 2)/2;
    while(parent_index >= 0)
    {
        maxheapify(arr, parent_index, size);
        parent_index--;
    }
}

void heapsort(int *arr, int size)
{
    buildheap(arr, size);
    while(size > 1)
    {
        swap(&arr[0], &arr[size - 1]);
        size--;
        maxheapify(arr, 0, size);
    }
}

void permutation(int *arr, int l, int r)
{
    
    FILE *fptr = fopen("heapsort_permutation.txt", "a");
    if(l == r)
    {
        for (int i = 0; i <= r; i++)
            fprintf(fptr, "%d\t", arr[i]);
        fprintf(fptr, "\n");
    }
    else
    {
        for(int i = l; i <= r; i++)
        {
            swap(&arr[i],  &arr[l]);
            permutation(arr, l+1, r);
            swap(&arr[i],  &arr[l]);
        }
    }
    fclose(fptr);
}

void heapsort_run(int n)
{
    FILE *fptr = fopen("heapsort_permutation.txt", "r"), *fout = fopen("heapsort_out.txt", "w");
    char *c = (char *)malloc(sizeof(char) * (2*n + 2)), *token;
    int *a = (int *)malloc(sizeof(int) * n), i = 0;
    while(fgets(c, (2*n+2), fptr))
    {
        token = strtok(c, "\t\n");
        while(token != NULL)
        {
            *(a+i) = atoi(token);
            token = strtok(NULL, "\t\n");
            i++;
        }
        heapsort(a, n);
        for(i = 0; i < n; i++)
            fprintf(fout, "%d\t", a[i]);
        fprintf(fout, "%d\n", count);
        i = 0;
        count = 0;
    }
    fclose(fout);
    fclose(fptr);
}

int main()
{
    FILE *fptr = fopen("heapsort_permutation.txt", "w");
    fclose(fptr);
    int n, *arr;
    printf("Enter size of array : ");
    scanf("%d", &n);
    arr = (int *)malloc(sizeof(int) * n);
    printf("Enter elements into the array :\n");
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        scanf("%d", &(*(arr+i)));
    permutation(arr, 0, n-1);
    heapsort_run(n);
    return 0;
}
